  "Maria earns $3,500 per month after taxes. She spends $2,000 on needs, $700 on wants, and saves $800. After 5 years of investing her monthly savings at 7% annual return, approximately how much will she have?": "",
  "~$57,400": "",
  "$80,000": "",
  "$35,000": "",
  "$48,000": "",
  "Using the future value of an annuity formula: FV = 800 × [((1 + 0.07/12)^60 - 1) / (0.07/12)] ≈ $57,400. Consistent saving with compound growth produces significantly more than just $800 × 60 = $48,000.": "",
  "James has assets worth $150,000 (home equity, car, savings) and liabilities of $95,000 (mortgage balance, student loans, credit card debt). What is his net worth?": "",
  "$245,000": "",
  "$95,000": "",
  "$150,000": "",
  "$55,000": "",
  "Net worth = Total Assets - Total Liabilities = $150,000 - $95,000 = $55,000. This figure represents James's actual financial position after accounting for all debts.": "",
  "Twin sisters both receive $10,000. Aisha invests hers at 8% annual return while Brittany keeps hers in a checking account earning 0%. After 20 years, approximately how much more does Aisha have than Brittany?": "",
  "$16,000": "",
  "~$36,600": "",
  "$50,000": "",
  "Aisha's investment grows to $10,000 × (1.08)^20 ≈ $46,610. Brittany still has $10,000. The difference is approximately $36,610, illustrating the enormous opportunity cost of not investing.": "",
  "Carlos pays $35/month for a gym membership he never uses. If he instead invested that amount at 7% annually for 30 years, approximately how much would he accumulate?": "",
  "~$42,600": "",
  "$12,600": "",
  "$100,000": "",
  "$25,000": "",
  "Using the future value of an annuity: FV = 35 × [((1 + 0.07/12)^360 - 1) / (0.07/12)] ≈ $42,600. Small recurring expenses, when redirected to investments, can grow into substantial sums through compounding.": "",
  "A recent college graduate has $30,000 in student loans at 5% interest and is offered a job paying $55,000/year. Using the Rule of 72, approximately how long would it take for her debt to double if she made no payments?": "",
